Talk about bringing the party to your house! An 11,000-square-foot California mansion that’s on the market for nearly $7 million comes with an epic backyard packed with its very own water park. Located in Granite Bay, on the outskirts of Sacramento, the seven-bedroom, nine-bathroom abode features a swim-up bar grotto, 15-plus waterfalls, a cascading infinity pool with a slide, a lazy river and a sunken fire pit. The colossal 100-foot waterslide leads from the patio straight into the pool. Situated on 7 acres of land, the listing says that this “resort-like” estate has what is “believed to be California’s largest pool.” The abode begins with a vineyard-lined driveway with sweeping views of treetops. Enter through a 12-foot-high door. There is an elevator that can then take you down to the game room, which also has wet bar. Other features of the home include an open-concept kitchen, a breakfast nook and a family room complete with double islands. There is also a second hidden kitchen, a coffee bar and a formal dining room with a wine wall, according to the listing. Outdoor features include disappearing doors that lead to the lanai with a grill. There is also a private guest cottage that comes with a kitchenette and laundry room. What’s more, there’s even a home theater and a six-car garage. Parmis Pourarian with Guide Real Estate holds the listing.